abstract: Former British Paralympian Victoria Aggar has resigned from the World Anti-Doping Agency's (WADA) Athlete Committee over the organization's handling of the Russian doping scandal.
snippet: Former British Paralympian Victoria Aggar has resigned from the World Anti-Doping Agency's (WADA) Athlete Committee over the organization's handling of the Russian doping scandal.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former British Paralympian Victoria Aggar has resigned from the World Anti-Doping Agency's (WADA) Athlete Committee over the organization's handling of the Russian doping scandal.
headline_main: Britain's Aggar Quits WADA Role Over Russia Scandal
headline_print_headline: Britain's Aggar Quits WADA Role Over Russia Scandal

abstract: The legal opinions were written during previous Democratic and Republican administrations by the Justice Department’s Office of Legal Counsel.
snippet: The legal opinions were written during previous Democratic and Republican administrations by the Justice Department’s Office of Legal Counsel.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Justice Department has released several internal legal opinions that could help bolster President Trump’s claim of executive privilege in barring Congress from interviewing witnesses and collecting documents from the executive branch.

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Friday, Dec. 13, 2019.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Friday, Dec. 13, 2019.
lead_paragraph: An article on Thursday about the political climate in Britain amid the election campaign  misstated the age of Queen Elizabeth II. She is 93 years old, not 95.

abstract: A Malaysian court Friday approved the extradition of a North Korean man to the U.S. to face money laundering charges in a case he says is politically motivated.
snippet: A Malaysian court Friday approved the extradition of a North Korean man to the U.S. to face money laundering charges in a case he says is politically motivated.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia — A Malaysian court Friday approved the extradition of a North Korean man to the U.S. to face money laundering charges in a case he says is politically motivated.
headline_main: Malaysian Court Approves US Bid to Extradite North Korean
headline_print_headline: Malaysian Court Approves US Bid to Extradite North Korean

abstract: Voters pick whichever candidate exhausts them less.
snippet: Voters pick whichever candidate exhausts them less.
lead_paragraph: There are two power blocs driving politics today. First, there’s the proletariat. These are the working-class voters who go to Trump rallies in the U.S. and powered Brexit and Boris Johnson’s campaign in the U.K. They see their best world receding and they want a tough guy to bring it back.

abstract: When China's top legislature criticized a Hong Kong court's rejection of a face mask ban there, some global firms began to fear the potential for mainland interference in commercial contracts, lawyers and finance executives said.
snippet: When China's top legislature criticized a Hong Kong court's rejection of a face mask ban there, some global firms began to fear the potential for mainland interference in commercial contracts, lawyers and finance executives said.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — When China's top legislature criticized a Hong Kong court's rejection of a face mask ban there, some global firms began to fear the potential for mainland interference in commercial contracts, lawyers and finance executives said.
headline_main: Beijing's Legal Influence Triggers Disquiet in Hong Kong Financial Sector
headline_print_headline: Beijing's Legal Influence Triggers Disquiet in Hong Kong Financial Sector

abstract: Lucas Hnath’s cunning new ghost story, about a psychic and her client, is a twisty yarn that won’t unravel.
snippet: Lucas Hnath’s cunning new ghost story, about a psychic and her client, is a twisty yarn that won’t unravel.
lead_paragraph: Good ghost stories are hard to spoil; even if you give away the surprises, you can’t unfeel the prickle on your neck. Uncanniness is indestructible.

abstract: The British pound surged more than 2% on Thursday as Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party looked set for a decisive election victory that markets believe makes an orderly exit from the European Union all but certain.
snippet: The British pound surged more than 2% on Thursday as Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party looked set for a decisive election victory that markets believe makes an orderly exit from the European Union all but certain.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The British pound surged more than 2% on Thursday as Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party looked set for a decisive election victory that markets believe makes an orderly exit from the European Union all but certain.
headline_main: Pound Soars as Johnson Heads for Landslide British Election Win
headline_print_headline: Pound Soars as Johnson Heads for Landslide British Election Win

abstract: The strong showing is vindication for Boris Johnson, who now has a chance to put his personal stamp on Britain, beginning with Brexit.
snippet: The strong showing is vindication for Boris Johnson, who now has a chance to put his personal stamp on Britain, beginning with Brexit.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prime Minister Boris Johnson and his Conservative Party won a commanding majority in the British Parliament, a striking victory that redraws the lines in British politics and paves the way for the country’s exit from the European Union early next year.

abstract: Brexit Party leader Nigel Farage said Britain would leave the European Union if Boris Johnson's Conservatives win the majority forecast in the exit poll, but it may not be the hard Brexit he had spent his political career campaigning for.
snippet: Brexit Party leader Nigel Farage said Britain would leave the European Union if Boris Johnson's Conservatives win the majority forecast in the exit poll, but it may not be the hard Brexit he had spent his political career campaigning for.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Brexit Party leader Nigel Farage said Britain would leave the European Union if Boris Johnson's Conservatives win the majority forecast in the exit poll, but it may not be the hard Brexit he had spent his political career campaigning for.
headline_main: UK's Farage: We Will Get Brexit, but Maybe Not the Right Brexit
